flowRoot.flowPara: and Python libraries to read and write them
Python can talk to practically all databases. Here are the most common libraries:
sqlalchemy - a generic SQL interface and Object Relational Mapper (ORM)
The builtin csv module and the data analytics library pandas read and write CSV files.
The builtin xml module has four different parsers. They produce the same tree data structure.
The pandas library is most convenient, for detailed manipulations check out xlrd.
The builtin json module parses all files, if the data is table-like,
The to-go library for parsing HTML pages is BeatifulSoup4
The Pillow library (PIL) reads and writes many common image formats and does some image processing.
